1 AN ACT concerning crimes, punishment and criminal procedure; relating
2 to theft; changing the culpability required for certain types of theft;
3 increasing the criminal penalty when the property is a motor vehicle;
4 amending K.S.A. 21-5801 and repealing the existing section.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. K.S.A. 21-5801 is hereby amended to read as follows: 21-
8 5801. (a) Theft is any of the following acts done with intent to
9 permanently deprive the owner of the possession, use or benefit of the
10 owner's property or services:
11 (1) Obtaining or exerting unauthorized control over property or
12 services;
13 (2) obtaining control over property or services, by deception;
14 (3) obtaining control over property or services, by threat;
15 (4) obtaining control over stolen property or services knowing, or
16 having reason to know, the property or services to have been were stolen
17 by from another; or
18 (5) knowingly dispensing motor fuel into a storage container or the
19 fuel tank of a motor vehicle at an establishment in which motor fuel is
20 offered for retail sale and leaving the premises of the establishment
21 without making payment for the motor fuel.
22 (b) Theft of:
23 (1) Property or services of the value of $100,000 or more is a severity
24 level 5, nonperson felony;
25 (2) property or services of the value of at least $25,000 but less than
26 $100,000 is a severity level 7, nonperson felony;
27 (3) property or services of the value of at least $1,500 but less than
28 $25,000 is a severity level 9, nonperson felony, except as provided in
29 subsection (b)(7);
30 (4) property or services of the value of less than $1,500 is a class A
31 nonperson misdemeanor, except as provided in subsection (b)(5), (b)(6),
32 (b)(7) or, (b)(8) or (b)(9);
33 (5) property of the value of less than $1,500 from three separate
34 mercantile establishments within a period of 72 hours as part of the same

