1 act or transaction or in two or more acts or transactions connected together
2 or constituting parts of a common scheme or course of conduct is a
3 severity level 9, nonperson felony;
4 (6) property of the value of at least $50 but less than $1,500 is a
5 severity level 9, nonperson felony if committed by a person who has,
6 within five years immediately preceding commission of the crime,
7 excluding any period of imprisonment, been convicted of theft two or
8 more times;
9 (7) property that is a firearm of the value of less than $25,000 is a
10 severity level 9, nonperson felony; and
11 (8) property that is mail of the value of less than $1,500 from three
12 separate locations within a period of 72 hours as part of the same act or
13 transaction or in two or more acts or transactions connected together or
14 constituting parts of a common scheme or course of conduct is a severity
15 level 9, nonperson felony; and
16 (9) property that is a motor vehicle of the value of less than $1,500 is
17 a severity level 10, nonperson felony.
18 (c) As used in this section:
19 (1) "Conviction" or "convicted" includes being convicted of a
20 violation of K.S.A. 21-3701, prior to its repeal, this section or a municipal
21 ordinance which prohibits the acts that this section prohibits;
22 (2) "mail" means a letter, postal card, package or bag sent through the
23 United States postal service or other delivery service, or any other article
24 or thing contained therein;
25 (3) "regulated scrap metal" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 2024
26 Supp. 50-6,109, and amendments thereto;
27 (4) "remote service unit" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 9-
28 1111, and amendments thereto, and includes, but is not limited to,
29 automated cash dispensing machines and automated teller machines; and
30 (5) "value" means the value of the property or, if the property is
31 regulated scrap metal or a remote service unit, the cost to restore the site of
32 the theft of such regulated scrap metal or remote service unit to its
33 condition at the time immediately prior to the theft of such regulated scrap
34 metal or remote service unit, whichever is greater.
35 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 21-5801 is hereby repealed.
36 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
37 publication in the statute book.

